The paper discusses population protocols, which are a model of distributed computing. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the complexity of solving simple tasks in this model, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces new techniques, which could fall under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
